## 4) UX: Home Tab Restructure (Core Screen)

### 4.1 The new Home stack (top-to-bottom)
**Section A — Next Up (always first)**
- If service day assigned: “Next Service Day” + next visit card (if scheduled)
- If not assigned: “We’re preparing your Service Day” card with CTAs:
  - **Build your routine**
  - **Add a service**
- If user has no routine: show “Start your routine” CTA

**Section B — This Cycle: Your Routine**
- A compact summary:
  - # of services active
  - next cycle handles usage (if applicable)
  - top 3 routine services as pills
  - CTA: “Edit routine”

**Section C — Suggested for Your Home (Smart Add-ons)**
- 2–4 cards (never more on Home)
- Each card includes:
  - service name
  - recommended default level (if applicable)
  - handle cost
  - “Why this is recommended” (one line)
  - “Add” (one tap)
  - “Not interested” (hide)

**Section D — Receipts / History preview**
- If no receipts: show a mocked “Handled Receipt” preview card
- If receipts exist: show last completed receipt card

### 4.2 What we remove from Home
- Multiple redundant empty-state cards (“no upcoming visits”, “0 recent”) stacked together.
- Anything that reads like “wait.” Home should always present action.

---

## 5) Add Service Drawer (The Growth Engine)

### 5.1 Entry points (must be consistent)
- Floating “+ Add” button on:
  - Home
  - Routine
  - Membership
  - Receipts
- Also accessible from Service Catalog list

### 5.2 Drawer structure
**Header:** “Add a service”  
**Subtext:** “Recommendations are tailored to your home.”

**Section 1 — Best Next (Top recommendations)**
- 4 items max
- Derived from property signals + coverage map + seasonality + history

**Section 2 — Seasonal / While We’re Here**
- 2 items max
- Only show if eligible and not spammy

**Section 3 — Browse All Services**
- CTA opens catalog (filtered for eligibility)

**Section 4 — Switching (placeholder for 3D Switch Kit)**
- If coverage map shows PROVIDER + OPEN_NOW/LATER:
  - show “Switch a service” entry (can route to an informational page now)
  - do not implement full switch flow unless already planned for 3D

### 5.3 One-tap add flow (critical)
Tap “Add” on a recommended service should:
1) Preselect:
   - SKU
   - default Level (from 3A + 3B signals)
   - default cadence (if routine service)
2) Show a compact confirmation sheet:
   - what’s included
   - handles cost
   - level selector
   - cadence selector (if routine)
   - “Add” confirm
3) If SKU requires guidance questions:
   - ask after confirm, in a quick 0–3 question sheet
4) Return user to Home with success toast + Undo option

**Undo (10 seconds):**
- Revert the last add action quickly to preserve trust.

