## 6) Suggestion System Requirements (Smart + Calm)

### 6.1 Eligibility rules (hard)
- If category is NA → never suggest
- If service conflicts with property (no yard, no pool) → never suggest
- If service is already in routine → don’t suggest as add-on (suggest level upgrade instead if relevant)
- If user marked “Not interested” → suppress for 90 days (configurable)

### 6.2 Relevance ranking (v1 heuristic)
Score candidates by:
- Coverage status:
  - NONE highest
  - SELF medium (only for high-pain chores list)
  - PROVIDER low (suggest switch gently later)
- Seasonality:
  - windows/gutters/pressure wash timed by season (simple month rules)
- Home sizing:
  - large homes might get windows/gutters suggestions more frequently
- History:
  - if user recently completed related service, suggest adjacent “while we’re here” only

### 6.3 Throttling & frequency caps (must-have)
- Home screen: max **4** suggestions visible
- Drawer: max **6** recommended total
- Suggestion impressions:
  - do not show the same suggestion more than **2 times in 14 days**
- Do not show more than **1 proactive suggestion card/day** as a push-style surface (Home counts as passive)

### 6.4 Feedback loop
Every suggestion card includes:
- “Hide” / “Not interested”
- Optional reason:
  - Already have someone
  - Not relevant
  - Too expensive
  - Not now

Store this to suppress and to refine later.

