## 7) Routine Screen Improvements (Expansion-friendly)

### 7.1 Draft routine vs active routine
If your current system blocks browsing until subscribe, Sprint 3C should adjust:
- Allow **Draft Routine** creation and editing before subscription.
- Gate “Activate schedule / assign service day / finalize” behind membership.

This is crucial: paywalling the catalog prevents the “feel the magic” moment.

### 7.2 In-routine surfaces
For each routine item:
- show level
- quick “Upgrade level” option (only if it adds clear value)
- show “Add adjacent service” (one card at bottom of routine screen)

---

## 8) Membership Page Growth Surfaces (Prime/Costco feel without spam)

### 8.1 Make membership value visible
Add a “Service Wallet” module:
- current membership tier
- included handles
- this cycle planned usage
- “bundle savings” concept if applicable (even if approximate)

### 8.2 Upsell that matches your brand
- “Add one more service to make your home fully handled”
- No discounts required; emphasize calm + time saved + consistency.

---

## 9) Receipts (Handled Receipts) as a Growth Surface

### 9.1 Receipt bottom module (only after delivery)
At the bottom of a receipt:
- “Recommended next time”
- “While we’re here next time”
- If courtesy upgrade occurred: “Update level going forward” CTA (from 3A)

Rules:
- max 1–2 suggestions per receipt
- must be tightly related to what was just done

